casebody.data:
Percy J. PRIOR, Oscar Carlson, et al., Appellants, v. SAILORS’ UNION OF THE PACIFIC et al., Appellees. No. 8180. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. June 22, 1936. H. W. Hutton, of San Francisco, Cal., for -appellants. Aaron Sapiro, of Los Angeles, Cal., and Albert Michelson and Milton Sapiro, both of San Francisco, Cal., for appellees.

Before GARRECHT and DENMAN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon stipulation of counsel for respective parties, ordered appeal dismissed, without costs to either party; mandate forthwith.
